<section id="development-perl-requirements">
<title>Requirements for Perl components</title>

<section id="development-perl-dirstruct">
<title>Directory Structure</title>

<para>
The directory structure for each perl component should follow the same
pattern.  The following outlines the directory structure during development.
The development structure does not have all of the directories that a release
will have.
</para>

<note>
<para>
Anything that can be automatically generated should <emphasis>never</emphasis>
be checked into the repository.
</para>
</note>

<note>
<para>
The contrib directory should not be checked into the repository.  All
contributed files
that belong in the contrib directory should be kept in the trunk/contrib
directory.
</para>
</note>

<variableList>
<varListEntry>
<term>version</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Contains the version information for the package.  Update automatically --
should never be hand edited.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>lib</term>
<listItem>
<para>
The src directory contains all of the source code specifically developed 
for this project.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>etc</term>
<listItem>
<para>
The etc directory should only exist if there are relavant configuration files
or other files needed by the package.  The configuration files should be
populated with default values that will work immediatly upon installation.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>README.txt</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Required.  The readme file must follow the format given in the templates
directory.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>Makefile.PL/Makefile</term>
<listItem>
<para>
The build file must have a minimum set of targets.  A sample Makefile.PL and
Makefile is
given in the templates directory.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>Dependencies</term>
<listItem>
<para>
This file lists the names of the contributed packages that can be found in contrib
that are required by this package.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>COPYRIGHT</term>
<listItem>
<para>
This file contains the Inca copyright and can be found in the templates
directory.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>MANIFEST.SKIP</term>
<listItem>
<para>
This file contains regular expressions used to prevent files that are in SVN
from ending up in a distribution. 
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>t</term>
<listItem>
<para>
This directory contains all of the tests for the modules.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
</variableList>

</section>

<section id="development-perl-buildfile">
<title>Makefile Requirements</title>

<para>
There are a few required targets for the Makefile in each package.
There is a sample build file that has all of the required targets implemented
in inca/admin/templates
</para>

<para>Required Targets</para>
<note>
<para>
A template Makefile.PL and Makefile file is provided and all of these targets have been
implemented.
</para>
</note>
<variableList>
<varListEntry>
<term>devel-help</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Should list all of these required targets with descriptions.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>realclean</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Takes you back to the files that belong in SVN.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>dist</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Creates a binary distribution.  
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>release-candidate</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Increments the major version and creates a branch.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>release</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Creates a tag.  A release cannot be edited!
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
<varListEntry>
<term>populate-contrib</term>
<listItem>
<para>
Copies the files from contrib in svn to contrib in this working copy.
</para>
</listItem>
</varListEntry>
</variableList>
</section>

